As for necro's dying out, I think it boils down to Necro/magi/druid/ whatever else, becomes a utility class on raids, not required to be successful, but just handy to have around. Thats probably the same reason as to why 60 mage's are fairly uncommon. Modrod duty = teh suck. Necro on twitching duty = teh suck. Druid doin nothing but backup heals = teh suck (yes, I spelt &quot;the&quot; like that on purpose). Alot of druids I know want to be prime healer, but are not willing to give up ports/sows/whatever, to be a cleric. Shrug. How many competant 60 necros do you know? Ones that can be Fom or close to, almost all the time, WHILE twitching clerics? I know 2, and only 2 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ah well. Don't flame me, I have never played a 60 druid or a 60 necro, just going by personal experience from raids/gimp raids/pickup groups, and friends.<br>
<br>
