<br>
I have to assume it was early 2000 which puts that poll before Kunark when mages WERE still gods in comparison to the other classes. Even for the first few months after Kunark was released we were still considered very powerfull. Then the epic power boost and we were gods again (as long as you had the epic). Then Velious came along with melee balancing and swung the balance way in the favor of the melee (who honestly had been getting the shaft for about 2 yrs). Luclin seems to have given the casters plenty of mobs where they can reign supreme again and with caster balancing in the works it will be interesting to see where things settle.<br>
<br>
As far as Mages on Fennin Ro and Rodcer Nife (the two I play on the most)...<br>
<br>
On Fennin I have not noticed much of a change. I see mages about as often as I normally used to on Rodcet. Pretty much consistant with what most polls show.<br>
<br>
On Rodcet I used to see &quot;typical&quot; (see above) ammounts of mages but lately I have noticed an increase in the number of high level mages. I'm thinking it could have to do with the number of high level guilds that need mages for their raids. It seems that Rodcet really does not have any obviously dominant &quot;uber&quot; guilds like some servers do. I mean we have guilds capable of doing the high level stuff, you just dont hear of them quite like you do on other servers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I've noticed more and more guilds comprised of only 50-55+ and each of these would need their handfull of mages.<br>
